This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) subfield of Computer Science, which is covered by the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper specifically focuses on the analysis of gender bias in machine translation, which suggests that it could also be classified under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Additionally, the paper uses coreference resolution datasets, which could potentially place it under the cs.CY (Computational Geometry) category. Finally, the paper presents an automatic evaluation method, which could also make it relevant to the cs.SD (Sound) category, which covers signal processing and machine learning techniques for audio and speech analysis.
